%% TrustyAI Service Operator - Data Flow Diagram
%% Generated by: Claude Opus 4.6

sequenceDiagram
    participant User as External User
    participant Route as OpenShift Route<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant OAuth as OAuth Proxy<br/>8443/TCP TLS
    participant TAS as TrustyAI Service<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant IS as KServe InferenceService<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Storage as PVC / Database<br/>Filesystem / JDBC
    participant Prom as Prometheus<br/>80/TCP HTTP

    rect rgb(200, 220, 255)
        Note over User,Storage: Flow 1: TrustyAI Service Model Monitoring
        IS->>TAS: POST /consumer/kserve/v2<br/>443/TCP HTTPS (internal cert)<br/>Model inference payloads
        TAS->>Storage: Store payload data<br/>PVC (filesystem) or<br/>Database (JDBC, optional TLS)
        Prom->>TAS: GET /q/metrics<br/>80/TCP HTTP plaintext<br/>Scrape trustyai_spd, trustyai_dir
        User->>Route: HTTPS/443 (TLS reencrypt)
        Route->>OAuth: Forward request
        OAuth->>OAuth: OpenShift SAR check<br/>pods/get in namespace
        OAuth->>TAS: HTTP/8080 (localhost)
        TAS-->>OAuth: Response
        OAuth-->>Route: Response
        Route-->>User: JSON Response
    end

    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant LMESCtrl as LMES Controller
    participant EvalPod as LMEval Pod<br/>+ Driver Sidecar
    participant S3 as S3 Storage<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Model as Model Endpoint

    rect rgb(220, 255, 220)
        Note over User,S3: Flow 2: LMEval Job Execution
        User->>K8sAPI: Create LMEvalJob CR<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS<br/>Bearer Token
        K8sAPI->>LMESCtrl: Watch notification
        LMESCtrl->>K8sAPI: Create evaluation Pod<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS<br/>ServiceAccount
        LMESCtrl->>EvalPod: exec (status check)<br/>SPDY/TLS ServiceAccount
        EvalPod->>Model: Evaluation requests<br/>configurable protocol
        EvalPod->>S3: Download data (offline mode)<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS<br/>AccessKey/SecretKey
    end

    participant GORCHRoute as OpenShift Route<br/>443/TCP HTTPS (edge)
    participant Orchestrator as Guardrails Orchestrator<br/>8032-8033/TCP HTTP
    participant Generator as KServe Generator<br/>configurable
    participant OTLP as OTLP Collector<br/>configurable

    rect rgb(255, 220, 220)
        Note over User,OTLP: Flow 3: Guardrails Orchestration
        User->>GORCHRoute: HTTPS/443 (TLS edge)<br/>No auth required
        GORCHRoute->>Orchestrator: HTTP/8032 or 8033<br/>plaintext
        Orchestrator->>Generator: Inference request<br/>configurable protocol
        Generator-->>Orchestrator: Response
        Orchestrator->>OTLP: Traces/metrics (optional)<br/>HTTP/gRPC configurable
        Orchestrator-->>GORCHRoute: Response
        GORCHRoute-->>User: JSON Response
    end
